          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a section of the Śivarayasya, a purāṇic-style, Tantric work. Text highlights the veneration of Śiva and especially his Vedic manifestation of Rudra, the Howler, through the employment of Vedic mantras. There is a post-colophon addition to the text (f. 10r-10v), also part of the Śivarayasya and dedicated to Rudra.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Rudranāmāvalī</title>
              <author>Bhaṭṭa Purāṇīka, Bālakṛṣṇa (Son of Nārāyaṇa)</author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śivarahasyoktarudramaṃtravibhāgavidhisamāptaḥ // (f. 10r).</colophon>
